                  "inline_data": null,
                  "text": "The brake wear indicators are illustrated in the **CL605-LANDING_GEAR** manual within the \"WHEELS AND BRAKES\" section. \n\n### **Image/Figure Reference**\nAn illustration showing the brake assembly and its components, including the wear indicators, can be found in:\n*   **Figure 15-10-8: Brakes and Lower Main Gear Structure**\n*   **Document:** Bombardier Challenger 605 - Landing Gear, **Page 15**\n\n### **Description of the Brake Wear Indicator**\nAccording to the manual (**Page 14**), each brake assembly is equipped with **two brake wear indicator pins** to provide a visual indication of brake wear. \n\n*   **Visual Check:** The indicator pins are located on the brake housing. \n*   **Servicing Requirement:** When the end of the wear indicator pin is **flush** with the top of the indicator housing, the brakes must be serviced.\n*   **Inspection Conditions:** To get an accurate reading, the pins must be checked under the following conditions:\n    1.  The **brakes must be applied**.\n    2.  **Hydraulic systems 2 and 3** must be pressurized.\n\nFor more details on the braking system, you can also refer to **Figure 15-10-9** (HYDRAULIC Synoptic Page) on page 15, which shows brake pressure indications.",
